I follow a "self-taught & don’t stop" mentality of constantly trying to better my skills.

As a research and user interaction advocate I help craft User Experiences that people love to come back to time and time again. I also work closely with product management, engineering and company leaders to successfully go from early stage product concepts to launch.

My work has been called "ground breaking", "a breath of fresh air" and "perfectly simple".

I recently finished working at Amazon on the Instant Video service where we launched Amazon Prime Video Direct. I'm currently at Digital Reasoning and consulting with my own UX Triage process around the United States.

UX Operations Director, Digital Reasoning
Mar 2018 - Current

Sr. Principal UX Designer, Avenel
May 2015 - Mar 2018

My team was responsible for everythign from simple workflows and intuative interfaces to branding and marketing.

Avenel is the first native iOS Electronic Health Record (EHR) that uses Machine Learning and AI to help alleviate provider burden.
Bolt News is a new paradigm in news consumption. Designed for iOS and Android, Bolt is designed to feel like a conversation about the news, rather than news being told to you.
UX Triage is the result of a deliberate & relentless pursuit to simplify the problem solving workflow for designers. Through the use of thoughtfully pure simplicity.

I worked as the Senior UX Designer. I met with indie filmmakers and content aggrigators to learn what kinds of tools and features they needed to be sucessful. I followed that up by working with the engineering teams doing domain modeling, then the front end devs doing component based UX design, along with extensive user studies and usabality testing.

Helping content creators and visual storytellers reach millions of Amazon customers across hundreds of devices with the same distribution options and delivery quality available to major motion picture and television studios.

The seemingly, impossibly, small wallet nok.

With nok we set out to make a wallet that carries ONLY what you need. With room for up to 3 cards and 1 ID, it only weighs 1 gram. Plus, a pocket for cash. nok is the result of a deliberate & relentless pursuit of pure functionality.
Prerunr is a SASS I built as a place for indie filmmakers to get feedback during post production.

Sr. UX Designer,
Patient Logic
Jun 2012 – Mar 2014

I managed and worked with a strong team and develop a world class Physician's Experience which include everything from logging in, to managing a patient's data, ordering medications and writing the physician's note (EHR).

I delivered Workflow Designs and Wireframes. I participated heavily in User Testing, Feature Planning, Scrum Planning, Team Management, and the Enterprise Level UX Architecture.

Sole Interactive Designer working on the National Guard account. I designed for the web site including work on internal software, and mobile apps.

Working with a team of programmers to built a user flow and architecture that works with an experiential design to inform and teach users about the benefits and concerns of joining the National Guard Special Forces.

Concept design for national campaigns reaching users through traditional advertising, social media and web experiences.

Collaborateed with a Creative Director, Art Directors, Account Executives and Designers to create usable, memorable, and powerful experiences.
